dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from the UNOCHA COD FOD Registry. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected where possible and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS:
1. Converted p-codes to match format in admin boundaries candidate: 2 characters for Admin 0 portion, 2 characters for Admin 1, 2 characters for Admin 2, 2 characters for Admin 3 and 3 characters for Populated Place 2. Created and populated a reference name field 3. Converted place names to proper case. Extra spaces were removed and open parentheses were closed 4. Changed admin 0 portion of p-codes from "MLI" to "ML" 5. Features with a class number ʺ5ʺ had their class description changed to a null value. Class number ʺ4ʺ features had their description changed to ʺAdmin3 Capitalʺ. Class number ʺ3ʺ features had their description changed to ʺAdmin2 Capitalʺ. Class number ʺ2ʺ features had their description changed to ʺAdmin1 Capitalʺ 6. Original downloaded file was missing a point with national capital attribution. Feature ʺBamako-Couraʺ with p-code ʺML090103000ʺ had its name changed to ʺBamakoʺ and its class description changed to ʺNational Capitalʺ. Its popPlaceClassNumber was changed from ʺ4ʺ to ʺ1" 7. Feature ʺS0Mankindy-Guemouʺ had its spelling changed to ʺSomankindy-Guemouʺ. Feature ʺAnam0laʺ had its spelling changed to ʺAnamolaʺ. 8. Admin names updated to match admin candidate 9. Features ʺYoloʺ and ʺNiamana Sobalaʺ had their 'admin1Pcode' changed to ʺML04ʺ 10. Admin name attribution fixed for feature ʺKoungobaʺ with p-code ʺML030701004ʺ. Admin 1 name changed to ʺSikassoʺ and Admin 2 name changed to ʺSikassoʺ 11. ITOS received new attribution from the IMO for Admin3 unit ʺSasalbeʺ. Populated places attributed to "Sasalbe" changed Admin2 attribution from ʺTenenkouʺ to ʺMoptiʺ. P-codes for Admin3 units in Admin2 ʺMoptiʺ and ʺTenenkouʺ have been updated to reflect this change
The following are known issues not addressed in this version:
1.146 points fall outside attributed admin 1 boundaries 2. 426 points fall outside attributed admin 2 boundaries 3. 1,799 points fall outside attributed admin 3 boundaries 4. 342 points exist with identical geometry to other points but different names 5. 327 points exist with identical geometry and feature names 6. 1,167 points exist with identical ʺfeatureName_frʺ values within the same lowest admin level (Admin3) 7. There were some place names that appeared to contain alternate names within parentheses or behind a forward slash. They may need to be separated from their names and put in an alternate name field.
